Network ACLs (NACLs) - AWS Solutions Architect Exam Guide
Kya hai Network ACL?
Network ACL ek subnet-level firewall hai jo virtual firewall ki tarah kaam karta hai. Ye decide karta hai ki kaunsa traffic subnet mein aa sakta hai aur kaunsa bahar ja sakta hai.
Key Points (Exam ke liye important!)
1. Subnet-Level Protection

Security Groups = Instance level
NACLs = Subnet level (poora subnet protect karta hai)

2. Stateless Nature üî¥ (Bahut Important!)

Inbound aur Outbound dono rules separately configure karne padte hain
Example: Agar port 80 pe inbound allow kiya, toh response ke liye outbound bhi allow karna hoga
Security Groups stateful hote hain, NACL stateless

3. Default NACL

Har VPC ke saath ek default NACL aata hai
By default sab kuch allow hota hai (inbound + outbound)

4. Additional Security Layer

Security Groups ke upar extra protection
Defense in depth strategy ka part

Exam Questions ke liye Scenarios:
Q1: Security Group vs NACL - Farak kya hai?

Security Group: Stateful, instance-level, only allow rules
NACL: Stateless, subnet-level, allow + deny rules

Q2: Agar ek subnet se traffic block karni hai toh?

NACL use karo (kyunki NACL mein deny rules hote hain)
Security Group mein sirf allow rules hote hain

Q3: Default NACL vs Custom NACL?

Default: Sab allow
Custom: By default sab deny (explicitly allow karna padta hai)

Rule Processing

Rules number order mein process hote hain (lowest first)
Pehla matching rule apply hota hai, baaki ignore
Rule numbers: 1-32766 (100, 200, 300... recommend karte hain gaps ke liye)

Exam Tip üí°
"Stateless" yaad rakho - ye sabse zyada poocha jaata hai exam mein!RetryMquesstion type asked in examEditAWS Solutions Architect Exam - NACL Questions ke Types
1. Comparison Questions (Sabse Common!)
Q: Security Group aur NACL mein kya difference hai?

Stateful vs Stateless
Instance-level vs Subnet-level
Allow-only vs Allow + Deny rules
Evaluation order

Q: Kab Security Group use karein aur kab NACL?

Specific instance = Security Group
Poora subnet block karna = NACL
Deny rules chahiye = NACL

2. Scenario-Based Questions
Scenario 1: Traffic Block karna hai
Q: Ek specific IP address (hackers ka) se aane wali 
traffic ko block karna hai. Kya use karoge?

Answer: NACL (kyunki deny rules chahiye)
Scenario 2: Stateless Behavior
Q: Tumne NACL mein port 443 inbound allow kiya. 
User ko response kyun nahi mil raha?

Answer: Outbound rule missing hai (NACL stateless hai)
Scenario 3: Rule Order
Q: Rule 100: Allow 10.0.0.0/16
   Rule 200: Deny 10.0.0.5/32
   Kya 10.0.0.5 se traffic aayegi?

Answer: Haan! (Rule 100 pehle match hoga)
3. Troubleshooting Questions
Q: EC2 instance internet access nahi kar pa raha. Security Group sab allow hai. Kya check karoge?

‚úì NACL outbound rules
‚úì NACL inbound rules (response ke liye)
‚úì Route table
‚úì Internet Gateway

4. Best Practices Questions
Q: Multiple subnets ke liye NACL kaise configure karein?

Ek NACL multiple subnets ke saath associate kar sakte ho
Lekin ek subnet sirf ek NACL ke saath

Q: NACL rule numbering best practice?

100, 200, 300... gaps chhodo
Future mein beech mein rules add kar sako

5. Default vs Custom NACL
Q: Naya VPC banaya, default NACL ka behavior kya hoga?

Sab traffic allow (inbound + outbound)

Q: Custom NACL banaya, default behavior?

Sab traffic DENY
Explicitly allow karna padega

6. Architecture Questions (Diagram-based)
Q: Is architecture mein security improve kaise karein?

Internet ‚Üí IGW ‚Üí Public Subnet (Web Server) 
                     ‚Üì
                Private Subnet (Database)

Answer: 
- Public subnet NACL: HTTP/HTTPS allow, baaki deny
- Private subnet NACL: Sirf public subnet se traffic allow
7. Port-Specific Questions
Q: Web application hai. NACL mein minimum kya allow karna hoga?
Inbound:
- Port 80 (HTTP)
- Port 443 (HTTPS)
- Port 1024-65535 (ephemeral ports for responses)

Outbound:
- Port 80, 443
- Port 1024-65535 (ephemeral ports)
8. Multiple Choice Tricky Questions
Q: NACL ke bare mein GALAT statement kaunsi hai?

A) Stateless hai ‚úó
B) Subnet level pe kaam karta hai ‚úó
C) Automatically return traffic allow karta hai ‚úì (YE GALAT HAI!)
D) Deny rules support karta hai ‚úó

9. Cost/Performance Questions
Q: NACL use karne se extra cost lagta hai?

Answer: NAHI! Free hai

Q: 100 rules vs 10 rules - performance difference?

Sequential processing hai, zyada rules = thoda slow
Best practice: Minimum necessary rules

10. Real-World Problem Questions
Q: DDoS attack ho raha hai specific IP se. Quick fix?
Answer: 
1. NACL mein deny rule add karo (lowest number)
2. Us IP ko immediately block kar do
3. Security Group mein nahi kar sakte (no deny rules)
Exam Tips üéØ
Yaad Rakhne Wale Points:

S.S.N.A - Security Group = Stateful, NACL = Stateless
Deny chahiye toh NACL
Lower number = Higher priority
Ek subnet = Ek NACL (but ek NACL = multiple subnets OK)
Ephemeral ports (1024-65535) outbound allow karna mat bhoolna!

Common Mistakes (Exam mein mat karna!):

‚ùå NACL ko stateful samajhna
‚ùå Outbound rules bhool jana
‚ùå Rule order ignore karna
‚ùå Ephemeral ports miss karna
‚ùå Security Group aur NACL confuse karna
